        <div class="twelve-columns">
            <h4>Simple Font Pairing Tips</h4>
            <p>Successfully pairing fonts can be an arduous task! Keeping in mind these few tips will help you get started.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row clearfix">
        <div class="four-columns column">
            <p><strong>The Skeleton</strong></p>
            <p>When considering the skeleton of the fonts, try to keep the width, x-height, and proportions similar.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="four-columns column">
            <p><strong>The Meat</strong></p>
            <p>The meat of a font is in reference to it's weight. While it may not seem apparent due to the thicker shape, good pairs will share similar skeletons regardless of its meat.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="four-columns column">
            <p><strong>The Contrast</strong></p>
            <p>A good way to provide contrast for your pairs, is choosing a sans-serif and serif font that share a similar skeleton with varying meat sizes.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>